Transcription.Text: "Anne, They have stolen our baby." It was not only their baby - it was America's. Toulouse-Lautrec At the Tate. Vigour and decay. By David Sylvester. What is singular about his use of them is that no other artist, of his time or any other, has painted them so directly, intime intimately and pertinently.
